explosion at bp oil refinery in scotland
    grangemouth, scotland, march 22 - 
an explosion followed by a fire ripped through a british petroleum
(bp) oil refinery, killing one man. a bp spokesman said the fire was
confined to one plant at the 700-acre refinery at grangemouth, 25
miles west of edinburgh. the cause and extent of the damage had yet to
be determined. two people were killed in a previous explosion and fire
at the plant on march 13. that incident is still being investigated,
the spokesman said. reuter 
